category: NAME THAT TOMB
category comment: 

clue: The imperial crypt of Dom Pedro I lies on the grounds of Independence Park in this largest Brazilian city

response: São Paulo

clue: This final resting place in Manhattan of a president & his wife is the largest mausoleum in North America

response: Grant's Tomb

clue: Cyrus the Great's tomb still stands at Pasargadae in this country, but his gold sarcophagus is gone

response: Iran

clue: The inscription on this conquistador's tomb in Puerto Rico reads, "Here rest the bones of a valiant lion"

response: Ponce de León

clue: The tomb of this father of modern China lies on Purple Mountain in Nanjing

response: Sun Yat-sen

